Business email FAQ

What is a professional business email?

A professional business email uses your custom domain, like yourname@yourbusiness.com, instead of generic services like Gmail or Yahoo. It represents your brand or business, makes your communication look credible and helps build trust with customers. Using a custom email domain aligns your emails with your business identity. Your business’ website domain should match your email’s, ensuring that when clients receive an email, they recognize it as coming from a legitimate source related to your company. If you don’t already have a website domain you can get a free domain with Wix for one year when you pair it with a website plan.

What are the benefits of a custom email domain?

A custom email domain offers many key advantages for your business. First, it enhances your credibility—customers are more likely to trust communications from a professional email address that matches your domain. It also strengthens brand consistency, ensuring every interaction reflects your business identity. Lastly, having a custom email domain gives you better control over your business communications, allowing you to manage email addresses, security settings and team accounts from a single, centralized platform.

What is email hosting?

Email hosting provides the infrastructure that allows businesses to manage their email accounts and communications. It’s a service that provides the servers for sending, receiving and storing emails using your custom domain. It lets you use a custom domain for your email addresses (like yourname@yourbusiness.com) instead of a generic provider. With email hosting, you get more control over your business communications, plus the added professionalism that comes with branded email addresses. It's a simple way to keep your emails organized, secure and aligned with your business identity.

What email is best for a business account?

The best email for a business account is one that uses a custom domain (e.g., yourname@yourbusiness.com) to create a professional and trustworthy impression. It should also offer important features like strong security to protect your communications, ample storage to handle all your business needs and reliable uptime so you never miss an important email. Services that provide these features, along with easy management tools and integration with other business applications, are perfect for a business email account.

Do small businesses need a business email?

Absolutely, having a business email is a must for small businesses. It helps you look professional and trustworthy to clients, customers and partners. Instead of using a generic business email address, a custom business email shows that you’re serious and makes it easier for people to connect your email with your brand. It’s a small detail that can really improve how you’re perceived and build stronger relationships. It’s important to match your business email with your website. If you don’t already have a site, you can create a business website with Wix here.

What is a good domain email?

A good domain email should be professional, easy to remember and closely aligned with your business name or brand. For example, something like info@yourbusiness.com or yourname@yourbusiness.com is ideal. The “yourbusiness” part should match your website’s domain. If you don’t already have one, you can use Wix’s domain name generator to search and register your domain. Once your email and domain match, this not only makes communication simpler but also helps reinforce your brand with every email you send.

How do I create my own email domain?

Creating your own email domain is pretty straightforward with Wix. First, use Wix’s domain name search to choose and register an available domain name. Next, choose an email hosting provider that supports custom domains. Finally, set up your email addresses using that domain. You can connect any domain, whether it’s one you purchased at Wix or a domain you purchased elsewhere.

With Wix, you can complete all of these steps and even go on to create your website, so that you have all your online assets in one place.

Will my email work on my mobile phone and tablet?

Yes, your business email will work seamlessly on both your mobile phone and tablet. Whether you’re using Android or iOS, you can easily set up your email to send and receive messages on the go. Most email providers offer apps or allow integration with your device’s built-in mail app, so you can manage your emails just as easily from your phone or tablet as from your computer.

Can I create a business email for free?

Wix offers custom business email services, but they aren’t free. However, you can get great email plans for your professional communication. If you do find a free business email, you’ll notice that most options come with limitations like fewer features, limited storage and less security. If you’re looking for a truly professional email with your custom domain (like yourname@yourbusiness.com), it’s worth considering a paid option. Paid plans usually offer better security, more storage and additional tools to help you manage your emails and business communications effectively.

Does Wix integrate with Google?

Yes, Wix integrates with Google Workspace, giving you access to professional tools like Gmail, Google Drive and Google Calendar.

Does Wix offer email forwarding?

Yes, Wix offers email forwarding. This means you can easily send emails from your custom address to another account, helping you manage your messages all in one place without missing any important emails. It’s a convenient way to stay organized while keeping your professional email address active.
